    {
      "id": "sybil_4_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_4",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a mechanically sound driver\u2019s car featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant. Crucially, the IMS bearing has been retrofitted with an LN Engineering ceramic solution, and the rear main seal (RMS) was replaced during the same service interval. Power is managed via a G96 6-speed manual transaxle, delivering linear torque to the rear wheels. The suspension geometry has been optimized with Bilstein B8 performance dampers, providing superior damping rates and chassis composure during high-G cornering. The braking system utilizes four-piston monobloc calipers paired with vented, cross-drilled rotors for consistent thermal management. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain maintains excellent compression and leak-down figures, making this an ideal candidate for a purist seeking a visceral, analog driving experience.",
